The paper deals with coding theory, specifically the Golomb-Welch conjecture and perfect error-correcting codes. This falls under the subfield of information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also uses techniques from combinatorics (cs.CC) and number theory (cs.NT) to derive its results. Additionally, the paper discusses the implications of its results for cryptography (cs.CR).
